{
  "texts": [
    "This dataset, based on the Freebase KG [9], consists of questions that require up to two or three-hop reasoning to identify the correct answer entity, utilizing Hits@k as the evaluation metric to determine if the top-k predicted answer is accurate.",
    "It includes approximately 1600 test samples.",
    "The vanilla ChatGPT (GPT-3.5) accuracy in zero-shot setting without any external knowledge is 61.2%.StructGPT [10] is a state-of-the-art approach that leverages LLM's capabilities for reasoning with evidence extracted from a KG.",
    "This method involves extracting a sub-graph from a KG by matching the topic entities in the question.",
    "The LLM is then directly employed to identify useful relations and extract relevant triples from the sub-graph, guiding it to effectively traverse and reason within the graph structure."
  ]
}